### Test Events API Endpoints
### This file can be used with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001

### 1. List all events (no userId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events

###

### 2. List all events with userId (marks favorites)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events?userId=user123

###

### 3. Get user favorites (empty initially)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites?userId=user123

###

### 4. Get user favorites without userId (should return 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites

###

### 5. Add event to favorites
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user123",
  "eventId": "event-001"
}

###

### 6. Add another event to favorites
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user123",
  "eventId": "event-002"
}

###

### 7. Get user favorites (should have 2 events now)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites?userId=user123

###

### 8. List all events with favorites marked
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events?userId=user123

###

### 9. Try to add non-existent event (should return 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user123",
  "eventId": "invalid-event"
}

###

### 10. Remove event from favorites
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites/event-001?userId=user123

###

### 11. Get user favorites (should have 1 event now)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites?userId=user123

###

### 12. Remove event without userId (should return 400)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites/event-002

###

### 13. Try to remove non-existent event (should return 404)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/favorites/invalid-event?userId=user123

###

### 14. Check Swagger documentation
GET {{baseUrl}}/api

###

### 15. Get specific event details (from events list)
# First get all events, then check individual event data
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events

###
